ost disturbing menace known to human kind</span><hr size=1> Kind of off-topic, but does anyone know much about Classical music? The old composers, their lives etc?  <br>
<br>
I remember having to read this article in class once, about a classical composer. A man who was absolutly brilliant, considered a Genius. Yet he, was basically a freak.  I can't remember everything my teacher mentioned about him, but one of his 'quirks', was that he couldn't wear anything but silk. Otherwise he'd get terrible rashes.  He'd also blow up over trivial things. I just can't remember what else the article mentioned about him. It was a very boring article. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :x --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/sick.gif ALT=":x"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
If I remember correctly, the point of the article, was that, most people in history, and perhaps even in modern times, who could be considered a &quot;genius&quot;, could also be considered 'freaks'.   That with their &quot;genius&quot; they also have some oddities that set them apart from others.  That maybe it had something to do with their brains...and dont' ask me what. I've fogotten most of that article.<br>
<br>
I'm not trying to make excuses for MJackson.  I find a lot of the stuff I hear about him disturbing. <br>
<br>
Yet, maybe he's just different, and not harmfull.  Then again, maybe he is.<br>
<br>
