<br>
Einstein.  Brilliant man.  Theory of Relativity.  Couldn't tie his own shoes.<br>
<br>
Stephen Hawking.  Another genius.  Debunks some of Einstein's theories.  Working on a Unifying Theory, to bring every single science under one common set of laws.  Crippled to the point where he's bound in a wheelchair, talks through a synthesizer, and yet verbally abuses his students and aids.<br>
<br>
Deaf, genius composers.<br>
<br>
&quot;Idiot&quot; Savants...can't hold a conversation, beat themselves at unfamiliar sights and sounds, but can perform calculations faster than a supercomputer.  (&quot;Rain Man&quot;)<br>
<br>
To dredge up more common examples...Almost all doctors and scientists (probably lawyers too, haven't checked that one) have a form of mild OCD (Obsessive compulsive disorder.)  In an extreme form, you get &quot;As Good as it Gets&quot; or the compulsive hand-washer, or the guy that stops his car after every block to make sure he hasn't run over a baby in the street.  In a mild form, it grants an attention to detail that you just can't find in the average human.  And, surprise surprise, OCD is also found most commonly in people of higher-than-average IQ's.  It's a chemical imbalance.  The switch that says you've done something and now you can move on, isn't there.  So you repeat it.  There are degrees.<br>
<br>
To unlock the brain allowing stimulation of certain neural pathways, it blocks others.  Chemicals are out of balance.  Genius on one hand, moron on the other.   When everything is in balance, you get a normal person with average intelligence.  When it's out of whack, you get the mentally retarded, or the super-genius.  Or shades of both.<br>
<br>
As to MJ...who can say?  Sure, we all choose what we let affect us.  What is a crippling life event to one might be an annoyance to brush off for another.  Being beaten as a child does not mean you will, in turn, beat your child...but it does pre-dispose one to it.  A person thinks it's normal.  Might even think that's how life is supposed to be.  Might rationalize it.  Or they may decide no child of theirs will ever undergo their own torture.  Personal choice.<br>
<br>
Now couple a traumatic upbringing with a chemical imbalance.  It's also rumored that he was injected with female hormones to prevent puberty, to retain his soprano voice.  All that HAS to do something to a person.  By traumatic, I don't just mean he might have been beaten or verbally abused.  That's in question.  His siblings don't report the same events (although siblings often have different views of their upbringing).  I mean, he was 12 years old and making 200k a month.  How many child stars do you see today living normal, well adjusted lives?  Please.  Take a child star, and never let him out of the spotlight.  Let him grow up in the public eye.  Give him more money than God, take away any semblance of a normal childhood...good grief, is it any wonder he's weird?<br>
<br>
In addition, a person's maturity is stunted during traumatic events.  Show me a 26-year old woman with a 5-year-old's voice, and I will show you a woman who was abused somewhere in her life.  Her outlook on relationships will reflect it, too.  (It's an example, don't get all snotty.)<br>
<br>
As to MJ sleeping with children...we're taught certain things are right and wrong.  We're conditioned to it culturally.  Our parents, our clergy, our friends and family all tell us and teach us good and bad, right and wrong, and what is or is not socially acceptable.  A parent looks disapprovingly on a child who speaks out of turn.  Spanks a child who hits another.  Whatever.  We are selfish creatures, as children.  We learn empathy, morals, and values.  They are not instinct.<br>
<br>
So where did a young Michael learn his values?  It's entirely possible he never lerned the difference between what is culturally acceptable and what is not.  Not as ingrained as it is in the rest of us.  Money is power, and it shelters a person from the outside.  I'm not saying no one ever told him &quot;You mustn't dangle your child from a balcony&quot;...I'm saying that, because of his stunted maturity, he is still as selfish as a child, and perhaps just never LEARNED to feel empathy for what other people go through.  No parenting instinct because he is still a child himself.<br>
<br>
Of course, everything I say, or anyone else, is merely heresay and spectulation.  Nobody ever knows anyones story. One 2- hour show can't grant us full access and a right to judge.  That's for courts who have time to sift through reams of evidence.<br>
<br>
But if he IS molesting children, I hope they fry him.   <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.familjenguild.com/dspMember.php?Name=Hildie"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.familjenguild.com/images/logo/hildie.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub27.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vendric>Vendric</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.bellatlantic.net/~vze26v7m/Images/Spanked.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:blue;'>Tavern Regular</span></span><br>  Posts: 347<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(2/8/03 7:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3109.topic&index=16>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The most disturbing menace known to human kind</span><hr size=1> They won't fry him. He'll pay them off, as he's done before. Great post btw <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  My post was just to see if I could rile some people up, and looking at garbhad above, it seems it worked <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Too easy, hehe...<br>
