<br>
Some parents do share a bed with their own young children. Though its not sexual.  You can read about their own views and opinions on it if you look up &quot;Attachment Parenting&quot;.<br>
<br>
Like you mentioned Hildie, some things are considered acceptable behavior, some things are not.  It wasn't all that long ago when familes all slept together.  In western society today, most families all sleep in seperate beds. (Except the parents.)<br>
<br>
I can accept that its normal for some families that do share a bed with their young children...in a non-sexual way. Yet, I can't find it normal that Michael Jackson would share his bed with children that are not even his own.<br>
<br>
Yet he claims its an innocent, loving gesture.  Different view points....different standards of whats normal and acceptable.  <br>
<br>
If he's not harming the children in any way, then I just continue to think its odd and abnormal.  If he is though, I just hope he can be 'caught' and stopped.<br>
